2.1 Preparation
===============

First of all, you must execute gtags(1)(*note gtags::) at the root of
source tree.  For example, if you want to browse the source code of Vi
editor in FreeBSD, please move to the source directory and invoke
gtags(1).


         $ cd /usr/src/usr.bin/vi
         $ gtags

   Gtags traverses sub-directories, picks up source files and makes
four tag files at the current directory.  After this, the whole files
under this directory is treated as a project.


         $ ls G*
         GPATH   GRTAGS  GSYMS   GTAGS

   * `GTAGS'         definition database

   * `GRTAGS'         reference database

   * `GSYMS'         symbol database

   * `GPATH'         path name database

   The `GSYMS' is for the symbols which are not defined in `GTAGS'.

   You should prepare for considerable disk space for the tag files.
For example, FreeBSD 7.0 kernel source code requires the following disk
space.

         source code(/usr/src/sys)       123MB

         GPATH                             1MB
         GTAGS                            26MB
         GRTAGS                           22MB
         GSYMS                            23MB
         -------------------------------------
         total of tag files               72MB


